### Secondary Issue: Kafka Connect Pod Restarts

The extremely high restart counts on `connect-0` (51) and `connect-2` (49) are a separate concern. From the logs you shared, an earlier crash was caused by:

```
TimeoutException: Timeout expired while trying to create topic(s)
```

This suggests the Kafka cluster was briefly unavailable or under load when those pods started. The Kafka cluster itself now shows Ready, so this may have been transient around the broker rolling restart on June 18. Worth monitoring whether the restart count continues to climb.
